         <abstract>
            <p>THE "Tocco" process of surface hardening, especially of the bearing surfaces of bus and truck crankshafts, is described in this paper. Desirable changes and modifications in production operations and their sequence made possible by the process are suggested. Examples are reported from service experience of the amount of resistance to wear and abrasion added to the bearing surfaces by this process.</p>
